# =============================================================================
# Translation (English → Hindi / Kannada / Telugu / Tamil)
# =============================================================================
#
# OPTION A — FREE, NO KEY (default, already works locally)
#   The app uses a built-in translate proxy at /api/translate with gtx fallback.
#   Run: npm run dev  →  switch language in Settings.
#   Optional: npm run i18n:translate  →  saves translations into locale JSON files.
#
# OPTION B — Google Cloud (better quality, optional)
#   1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
#   2. Create a project (free).
#   3. Enable "Cloud Translation API" (APIs & Services → Library).
#   4. Billing: new accounts get ~$300 free credit; Translation has a small
#      monthly free tier — card may be required but you won't be charged if
#      you stay within free limits. See:
#      https://cloud.google.com/translate/pricing
#   5. APIs & Services → Credentials → Create credentials → API key.
#   6. Restrict the key to "Cloud Translation API" only (recommended).
#   7. Copy the key into .env.local (NOT committed to git):
#
# GOOGLE_TRANSLATE_API_KEY=your_key_here
#
# Never use VITE_ prefix for this key — it must stay server-side only.
#
# Optional: custom translation endpoint instead of /api/translate
# VITE_TRANSLATE_API_URL=https://your-backend/translate
